.TH QIFTOP 1 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
qiftop \- Qt6 real\-time network traffic monitor (per\-interface and per\-connection)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qiftop
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qiftop
is a graphical, iftop\-style network monitor with two live views:
.IP \(bu 3
.B Interfaces
\(em per\-interface throughput, totals, link state, addresses and
error/drop counters.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Connections
\(em active flows with rates, totals, direction, reverse DNS, and optional
grouping by interface, process or container.
.PP
On startup qiftop tries to use the privileged
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
over system D\-Bus. When the agent is unavailable or access is denied (see
.B SECURITY
in
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)),
qiftop can fall back to in\-process capture and offer to relaunch with
elevated privileges via
.BR pkexec (1)
or
.BR sudo (8).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interface " " \fIiface\fR
Open on the Connections tab and show only flows on \fIiface\fR. May be
given more than once. The filter is not saved and mirrors
.BR iftop (8)'s
.BR \-i .
.TP
.B \-\-tray
Start in the system tray with a live throughput sparkline. Used by the
XDG autostart entry installed from
.IR "Settings \(-> Tray \(-> Start on login" .
Click the tray icon to summon the window.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-agent
Skip the agent and use in\-process capture. Intended for development and
debugging; per\-connection capture needs root or the self\-elevation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Print diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show built\-in help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH INTERFACE
Both tables are sortable by clicking a column header. The Connections view
accepts a filter expression (the same mini\-language documented in
.BR nqiftop (1));
right\-clicking a header toggles column visibility. Layout and view settings
are saved between runs. Throughput is formatted in IEC units (KiB/s,
MiB/s, ...).
.PP
A colour theme can be chosen under
.IR "Preferences \(-> Colors \(-> Theme" .
The default
.B System
leaves the native Qt palette untouched; named themes (Dark, Light, Nord,
Solarized, Gruvbox) apply immediately.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/qiftop/qiftop.conf
Per\-user settings.
.TP
.I ~/.config/autostart/qiftop.desktop
XDG autostart entry, created/removed by the "Start on login" preference.
.SH SECURITY
Live per\-connection data is root\-only on most systems (the conntrack
table exposes every host's flows). Prefer running the unprivileged GUI
against
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
and joining the
.B netdev
group rather than running qiftop as root. See
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
for the agent's access model and the configurable process\-detail
disclosure policy.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nqiftop (1),
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5),
.BR iftop (8),
.BR pkexec (1)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop/issues
